Saturday October 5th 2013 7:46 am -04:00,UnaI needed to learn how to open & read a file to understand how my code was going to work. Also so that I could see what was in a file. You will use open() and .read() in IDLE  NOT in the code in the body of your function read_words(words_file).The only thing that should be in the body of your function is the code you write to return a list made of the words in the file wordlist1.txt .So in the end  1. You will call your function read_words() in IDLE 2. IDLE will run your code that you wrote in the body of the  read_words(words_file) function3. and a list of words will be returned., Unresolved,1
