Saturday October 5th 2013 8:44 am -04:00,IDLE can not locate your filesThe first thing you need to do is:Find where your files are located (the file path) and then point the IDLE shell to the directory (file path) that wordlist1.txt  is in.Putting all your files in one folder and naming it Assignment3 will help keep you organized (as suggested by Hamish).In Hamishs example he used this:>>>import os>>> os.chdir(C:\\Projects\\Learning To Program\\Assignments\\Assignment3)The file path where your stored your files will probably be different. For example this was mine :>>>import os>>> os.chdir(C:\Python33\Assignment3) You can also point the IDLE shell to  a file path by assigning it a variable (<----this is what Paul showed us in the video lecture)For example:file = C:\ Python33\Assignment3\wordlist1.txt After IDLE knows where to find the file you want it to retrieve then you can open and read the file.I hope this helps ! :), Unresolved,0
